*===========================*
|    MooseX-Getopt-Usage    |
*===========================*

Perl Moose Role to use along with MooseX::Getopt to provide a usage printing
method that inspects your classes meta information to build a (coloured) usage
message including meta information.


SYNOPSIS

 use Moose;
 with 'MooseX::Getopt::Basic', 'NuFoo::Role::GetoptUsage';
 $self->getopt_usage;


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install

Note on systems with checkinstall use

    checkinstall ./Build install

If you want to create an uninstallable package.


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

You can find documentation for this module with the perldoc command.

    perldoc MooseX::Getopt::Usage

The source code and other information is hosted on github:

    http://github.com/markpitchless/moosex-getopt-usage


